- Use `dotnet new mvc -n MySecureApp` to create a new ASP.NET Core MVC project.
- Update your project file to target the latest LTS version of .NET Core or .NET 6+.
- Configure authentication in `appsettings.json`:
  ```json
  "Authentication": {
    "DefaultAuthenticateScheme": "Cookies",
    "DefaultSignInScheme": "Cookies",
    "DefaultChallengeScheme": "AzureAD"
  },
  "AzureAd": {
    "Instance": "https://login.microsoftonline.com/",
    "Domain": "yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com",
    "TenantId": "your-tenant-id",
    "ClientId": "your-client-id"
  }
  ```
- Add authentication services in `Startup.cs`:
  ```csharp
  public void ConfigureServices(IServiceCollection services)
  {
      services.AddAuthentication(AzureADDefaults.AuthenticationScheme)
          .AddAzureAD(options => Configuration.Bind("AzureAd", options));
      services.AddControllersWithViews();
  }
  ```
- Apply `[Authorize]` attribute to controllers or actions to restrict access.
- Use `RedirectToLogin` method in your controller to redirect unauthenticated users:
  ```csharp
  public IActionResult Login()
  {
      return RedirectToAction("Index", "Account");
  }
  ```
- Ensure you have the necessary NuGet packages installed, such as `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.AzureAD.UI`.
